article.headline: Ball St. 73, Indiana St. 70, OT
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. (AP) -- D'Andre Peyton scored a game-high 22 points on 8-of-16 shooting and grabbed seven rebounds as Ball State held off Indiana State 73-70 in overtime Saturday. Peyton's 3-pointer with 15 seconds left in overtime gave the Cardinals a 72-69 lead and forced Indiana State to foul. Skip Mills added 14 points and five rebounds for the Cardinals (3-4). Jay Tunnell led Indiana State (4-3) with 20 points on 9-of-10 shooting and 12 rebounds. Gabriel Moore added 19 points for the Sycamores and hit a 3-pointer with six seconds left in the game to force overtime. The Cardinals were outrebounded 38-37, but scored 17 points off 21 Indiana State turnovers. Ball State finished 20-of-29 (69 percent) from the free-throw line.
